Fragmented

Application which will create fragmented file to how many extents you will specify.
All info about params you will find by executing application: ./fragmented -h.

MAKE: 
To make this app, just type make. No special libraries are needed.

RUN:
To run this app, just write ./fragmented and you will get more info typed in app
help.

EXAMPLE:
To create file, which consists from 5 extents, file content will be @ and 
file will be stored in /mnt/data/file, run:

./fragmented /mnt/data/fragmented -c 5 -d 64